Title: "When Peace Found a Perch"

Quiet hearts whisper, ink-dipped dove soars;
Within grit and grind— hope unfurls, war snores.

Title: Reclaimed Verses in London's High Court 

Discourse, a weapon, yet survival, the potent art;  
In adversity, we find a fresh start.

Title: "In Unity, We Persist"

In Manchester's trials, blooms resilience, bright;
Pandemic woe fuels hope's resplendent flight.
